net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.composite.editor

Interface ValueChooserDisplayHandler<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the value type.

    public interface ValueChooserDisplayHandler<V>
    Handler for ValueChooser display requests.

    Implementors will receive the ValueChooser UI and it is there responsibility to place the chooser in the application UI.

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@proteus.co)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void displayChooser(ValueChooser<V> defaultChooser)
      Called to indicate that the specified chooser is to be placed in the application's UI for selection of a value.

    • Method Detail

      • displayChooser

        void displayChooser(ValueChooser<V> defaultChooser)
        Called to indicate that the specified chooser is to be placed in the application's UI for selection of a value.

        Implementations may choose to discard the chooser provided and provide their own. If you do this, please call the ValueChooserEditor.setUIValue(Object) method instead of the ValueEditor.setValue(Object) so the editor knows that the UI state has been modified.

        It is the responsibility of the implementor to close the chooser after the necessary selections are made or the user cancels the operation.

        Parameters:
        defaultChooser - the chooser.
